definition: to be born/to give birth/life/to grow/raw/uncooked/student
Four great beards of Beijing opera, namely: Ma Lianliang 馬連良|马连良, Tan Fuying 譚富英|谭富英, Yang Baosen 楊寶森|杨宝森, Xi Xiaobo 奚嘯伯|奚啸伯

sentences.english: You must now generate some events to see data in the dashboard.
sentences.chinese: 您現在必鬚生成一些事件，以在儀表板中查看數據。

sentences.english: This is why the Lord Jesus told Nicodemus that he had to be born into the kingdom of God.
sentences.chinese: 這就是何以主耶穌對尼哥底母說，他必鬚生入神的國。

sentences.english: Ceausescu decreed that all women must bear five children.
sentences.chinese: 奇奧賽斯庫頒佈法令要求所有的女人必鬚生5個孩子。

sentences.english: Performances have to born in a very prominent role.
sentences.chinese: 鬚生在表演中作用極爲突出。

sentences.english: There was no stacking fault in the direction perpendicular to the growth orientation.
sentences.chinese: 在垂直於晶鬚生長方向上沒有層錯的存在。

sentences.english: People must live, love can depend on.
sentences.chinese: 人必鬚生活着，愛才有所附麗。

sentences.english: We need to produce more textiles, especially silk and cotton.
sentences.chinese: 我們必鬚生產更多的織物，尤其是絲和棉。
